                   "message":  "SAVE-STATUS-SOURCE-NEUTRAL: rename scene_file_name -\u003e source_name, \"No scene\" -\u003e \"No file\"\n\nSource-neutral wording cleanup for the bottom status bar, now that the open save\nsource can be a .rge-scene OR a .rge-project (since #274 / #275):\n- SaveStatusSnapshot::scene_file_name -\u003e source_name (editor-state def + docs,\n  editor-shell producer + tests, editor-ui read + tests).\n- save_status_line\u0027s empty-state string \"No scene\" -\u003e \"No file\" (the None case =\n  no save source of any kind; a .rge-project isn\u0027t a \"scene\"). The \" *\" dirty\n  marker is unchanged.\n- Ported the loosely-scene-named test fns / comments in the same surface\n  (no_scene_* -\u003e no_source_* / no_file); the genuinely scene-specific tests\n  (which exercise SaveSource::Scene) keep their names.\n\nCosmetic only — no behavior change beyond the rendered empty-state word.\n7 files, 0 Cargo.toml. `rg \u0027scene_file_name|No scene\u0027` over crates is empty.\n(Chosen neutral names source_name / \"No file\"; trivially swappable if a\ndifferent word is preferred.)\n\nGate: VERIFY OK (7/7), 10/10 arch lints.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e",
